WEBVTT

00:00:00.880 --> 00:00:04.960
Hi everybody and welcome. My name is Alex Chisholm and I'm the product manager for

00:00:04.960 --> 00:00:09.520
Posit Cloud here at Posit. In this first installment of Posit Cloud Essentials,

00:00:09.520 --> 00:00:13.120
we're going to cover everything you need to know about getting started with a free account

00:00:13.120 --> 00:00:19.120
in just a few clicks. Posit Cloud is an online platform where you can do and share data science

00:00:19.120 --> 00:00:24.240
in your favorite coding and languages, all from the comfort of your web browser. In essence,

00:00:24.240 --> 00:00:29.840
Posit Cloud makes it easy for you to manage a variety of data projects in siloed, reproducible,

00:00:29.840 --> 00:00:35.680
environments that contain your code, your data, and your results, all of which can be shared.

00:00:36.880 --> 00:00:40.160
A space in Posit Cloud serves as the building block for the tool.

00:00:42.240 --> 00:00:48.000
You can create R projects in the RStudio IDE or work natively with Python and Jupyter.

00:00:49.040 --> 00:00:53.759
You can publish data applications and documents from cloud or from an external environment,

00:00:53.759 --> 00:01:00.000
such as RStudio Desktop or VS Code. You can also securely store database connections to

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.720
power your projects and outputs using a set of 16 included professional drivers.

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:10.720
Finally, you can invite members to your space to collaborate on work or to simply showcase

00:01:10.720 --> 00:01:16.080
your results, all the while keeping your eye on usage analytics for specific pieces of content.

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:22.400
Posit Cloud is a freemium tool. This means that you're able to create a free account and gain

00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:27.919
access to all of its functionality. If you happen to run into limitations in terms of compute power

00:01:27.919 --> 00:01:33.279
or number of published outputs, feel free to explore the affordable and flexible paid plans.

00:01:34.320 --> 00:01:39.120
On today's demo, we're going to create a free account, set up our first space,

00:01:39.120 --> 00:01:43.599
and then do some real work. Let's get started by going to Posit.Cloud.

